@startuml Activity Diagram - Image Scanning Process
!theme cerulean-outline

title SmartMedia - Image Scanning & Processing Activity Diagram

|User|
start
:Click "Add Photos" button;

|System|
:Show file picker dialog;

|User|
:Select image files;

|System|
:Store file paths in\ndiscoveredImages[];

:Navigate to\nScanningScreen;

|Processing Engine|
fork
  :Initialize Python\nengine (if needed);
  if (Model loaded?) then (No)
    :Load Qwen2-VL model;
    note right: Takes ~5-10 seconds\nfirst time only
    :Model ready;
  else (Yes)
    :Use existing model;
  endif
fork again
  :Display scanning UI\nwith progress;
end fork

repeat :Get next image from queue;
  
  |Processing Engine|
  :Read image file;
  
  if (File accessible?) then (No)
    :Mark as failed;
    :Log error;
  else (Yes)
    :Resize image to 224x224;
    
    :Calculate image hash\n(for duplicate detection);
    
    partition "AI Analysis" {
      :Pass image to\nQwen2-VL model;
      
      fork
        :Detect objects;
        :Generate object list;
      fork again
        :Analyze scene;
        :Determine indoor/outdoor;
        :Identify location type;
      fork again
        :Generate caption;
        :Create short description;
        :Create detailed description;
      fork again
        :Extract tags;
        :Generate keywords;
      fork again
        :Detect text/characters;
        :OCR if present;
      end fork
      
      :Combine AI results;
    }
    
    partition "Album Categorization" {
      if (Contains screenshot keywords?) then (Yes)
        :Category = "Documents";
      elseif (Single face + portrait?) then (Yes)
        :Category = "Selfies";
      elseif (Multiple faces + event?) then (Yes)
        :Category = "Events";
      elseif (Landscape/outdoor?) then (Yes)
        :Category = "Locations";
      else (None match)
        :Category = "Others";
      endif
    }
    
    partition "Face Recognition" {
      if (face_recognition installed?) then (Yes)
        :Detect faces using\ndlib library;
        
        if (Faces found?) then (Yes)
          :Extract face encodings\n(128-d vectors);
          
          repeat :Compare with\nexisting faces;
            
            if (Match found?\n(distance < 0.6)) then (Yes)
              :Add to existing person;
              :Update face album;
            else (No)
              :Create new person entry;
              :Generate new face ID;
            endif
          repeat while (More faces?) is (Yes)
          ->No;
          
          :Detect emotions\nfrom faces;
          
          :Save to FaceDatabase;
        endif
      else (No)
        :Use Qwen2-VL for\nface count only;
        note right: Face recognition is optional
      endif
    }
    
    :Compile metadata object;
    
    :Save to SQLite database;
    
    |System|
    :Broadcast result to UI;
    
    |User Interface|
    :Add image to gallery;
    
    :Update progress indicator;
    
    if (User viewing gallery?) then (Yes)
      :Show new image\nin real-time;
    endif
  endif
  
  backward :Increment progress counter;

repeat while (More images in queue?) is (Yes)
->No;

|Processing Engine|
:Mark processing as complete;

:Clear processing state;

|System|
:Send completion notification;

|User Interface|
if (User in ScanningScreen?) then (Yes)
  :Show "Processing Complete"\nmessage;
  
  :Enable navigation button;
  
  |User|
  :Click "View Gallery";
  
  |System|
  :Navigate to HomePage;
else (No)
  :Show desktop notification;
endif

:Display all processed\nimages in gallery;

stop

note right of "AI Analysis"
  **Processing Time per Image**
  • First: 25-30 seconds
  • Subsequent: 20-25 seconds
  • Face detection: +2-5 seconds
end note

note left of "Album Categorization"
  **Smart Categories**
  1. Documents (screenshots, text)
  2. Selfies (single person portraits)
  3. Events (multiple people, parties)
  4. Locations (landscapes, travel)
  5. Others (general photos)
end note

note right of "Face Recognition"
  **Face Matching Process**
  • Extract 128-d encoding
  • Compare with all existing faces
  • Threshold: 0.6 for same person
  • Lower = more similar
  • Create albums per person
end note

@enduml
